The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Focus on Kashyap
                                                                                                                       7                                      Focus on Kashyap
                                  
	Guangzhou: Indian men shuttlers sans national champion Chetan Anand will have a tough task at hand when they take on formidable Chinese Taipei in the first round of the Asian Games badminton event while the women too have drawn a tough opponent in Indonesia.         
	In the absence of Chetan, the onus will be on P. Kashyap who will play the second singles against Hsueh Hsuan Yi, the Asian and World Championship quarter finalist, after Arvind Bhat faces Hsieh Yu Hsing in the opener.         
	The medal hopes in the womens team event will largely depend on the form of world No. 3 Saina Nehwal, who comes into the Games after winning the singles gold in the Commonwealth Games and needs to be at her best when India clash with a strong Indonesian outfit.         
	Saina is to open the campaign against Adriyart Firdasari while Jwala Gutta and Ashwini Ponnappa, who won the womens doubles gold at the Delhi CWG, will take on Polii Greysia Jauhari Meiliana.         
	Meanwhile, the Indian womens hockey team, that finished third in the 2006 Doha Games, will play Malaysia in their opening seven-team round-robin tie on Saturday. The main threats for the Indian women are hosts China and South Korea, according to coach Sandeep Somesh.         
	The countrys campaign also starts in the cue sports, led by Pankaj Advani and Geet Sethi. Their main rival will be C Praprut of Thailand who has a record three Asian Games gold medals in his kitty.         
	In the table tennis team event, Indian men are clashing with Chinese Taipei in Group D while the women are crossing swords with Laos and then Singapore in Group B.         
	In shooting, led by Abhinav Bindra and Gagan Narang, the Indians will look to carry forward their CWG form.(agencies)                                                                                                                     
